 The deprecated functions ns_sprintrrf, ns_printrr and fp_nquery fail to
 enforce the caller-supplied buffer length, and can result in an
 out-of-bounds write when printing TSIG records. The TSIG case uses
 sprintf() without checking buflen. Remove the incorrect TSIG handling
 code that performs the unbounded sprintf write.
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/pipermail/libc-alpha/2026-April/177040.html
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=34033
Author: Florian Weimer <fweimer@redhat.com>
